cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.CC, cs.MM 

The paper deals with information theory and communication channels, which suggests cs.IT as the most likely category. The use of typical sets and entropy inequalities also points towards cs.NI and cs.SI. The paper also mentions the blowing-up lemma, which is commonly used in computational complexity theory, making cs.CC a possible category. Finally, the application of the results to a specific case involving binary channels suggests cs.MM as a possible category.
